Smaller factorials divide larger factorials, so the smallest formula_72 occurring in that linear combination will also divide the whole of formula_65. We get that formula_72 from the lowest power formula_70 term appearing with a nonzero coefficient in formula_78, but this smallest exponent formula_62 is also the multiplicity of formula_80 as a root of this polynomial. formula_81 is chosen to have multiplicity formula_82 of the root formula_83 and multiplicity formula_84 of the roots formula_85 for formula_86, so that smallest exponent is formula_87 for formula_88 and formula_89 for formula_90 with formula_91. Therefore formula_92 divides formula_65.

