====Conclusion====

Choosing a value of that satisfies both lemmas leads to a non-zero integer formula_118 added to a vanishingly small quantity formula_119 being equal to zero: an impossibility. It follows that the original assumption, that can satisfy a polynomial equation with integer coefficients, is also impossible; that is, is transcendental.

===The transcendence of ===
A similar strategy, different from Lindemann&#x27;s original approach, can be used to show that the number is transcendental. Besides the gamma-function and some estimates as in the proof for , facts about symmetric polynomials play a vital role in the proof.

For detailed information concerning the proofs of the transcendence of and , see the references and external links.

